<br>
About four blasts from your AE should kill most.<br>
Also, you do not need to quad to learn. start working on pulling one or two down to the beach at a time. when you can take those add another.<br>
<br>
Tips for quading in CS: Between the chief and the merchants is a very large expanse of land. if you have any kind of extra run speed (jboots or innate run 3) you will be able to easily out run the snared wyverns.<br>
<br>
Cast. run. and stop on spell refresh to cast again. Works great. If you have SoW you will need to time it better due to the fact that you will out distance them (and cause them to warp when low on life)<br>
<br>
if you have your flux staff, just hit that till out of range and wait till they get into range.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://mdar.homestead.com/files/fategif.gif" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=lordbug>LordBug</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 726<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/20/03 6:52 am)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 51 and clueless</span><hr size=1> Best plan now is to go to Kael with some friends and slaughter giants.  Get that CoV faction up.  If you can somehow shadow a Tormax or Avatar raid, DO IT.  Tag all their pulls and leech faction.  Raids generally don't mind as long as you stay out of the way and don't screw up their positioning.  The +CoV faction hit off each of these guys is at least one entire rank, maybe 2.<br>
<br>
Once you aren't KoS to CoV, go to town on the wyverns in CS.  Sometimes you won't find any up.  Last night, I found all of them up.  You can try the Othmir too, but you need to be damn fast on that snare.  They are almost always SoW'ed.  Even just solo'ing them, the XP is decent and the sellables can make you some cash (just don't sell the armor gems).  Also, learn the paths and times of the Cobalt Drakes.  They agro if you're attacking a wyvern.  They have a nasty close range AE(?).  Run like hell if you agro one.<br>
<br>
PoP planes... good luck.  I don't think I've ever had anyone below 53 in a PoP group.  PoN/PoD/PoI are worth the travel time if you have a group there.  Definately don't pass up the opportunity if it comes up.<br>
<br>
Velk's, KC, and Sebilis are all good spots too, but they are rather empty anymore.  You can easily teleport close to each of these, you just have to find people willing to go with you. <p><BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=26448">Ebdain Ahriman</a><BR>
