<br>
My wizard is 52 and I have gone back to KC to get pick up groups. Other zones take too long to get pick up groups. If I can play for 3-4 hours, then I take guildies with me to the other zones mentioned in this thread.<br>
<br>
If you don't have them yet, get your SoTF and Jboots. Or if you rich, go buy the Tboots for 6k.<br>
<br>
To practice, go somewhere easy and known to you. I was hunting in LOIO when I got my Bonds of Force so thats where I started to learn to single kite and later came back to learn how to quad kite.<br>
<br>
LOL, I am still 52 since I am trying to get run speed max'd. Experience is so slow these days, I just log on, play my allotted time and not even worry about the amount of exp gained. If I keep checking the exp, I get really frustrated.<br>
<br>
Good luck to ya. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=llith>Llith</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist</span><br>  Posts: 992<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/20/03 4:01 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: re:51</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>It's easy not to hit the otters, just stay clear of them and turn around to look before casting (use mouse to turn, arrow keys will get you killed).<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
